cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SE 

This paper is primarily focused on privacy and security in mobile devices, which falls under the category of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the study involves analyzing user behavior and decision-making, which is relevant to the "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. The use of machine learning and classifiers to make privacy decisions aligns with the "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The study also involves analyzing the contextuality behind user privacy decisions, which is relevant to the "cs.CY" (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves building a system to automatically grant appropriate resource requests, which falls under the "cs.SE" (Software Engineering) sub-category.
